Zambian Copper Output Falls in First Four Months, Reuters Says

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-06-09T12:08:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/zambian-copper-output-falls-in-first-four-months-reuters-says.html
Copper production in  Zambia ,  Africa ’s
largest producer of the metal, fell 9 percent in the first four
months of 2011 from a year earlier,  Reuters reported .  Output of the metal between January and the end of April
declined to 242,284 metric tons from 266,373 tons, the  news
agency  said, citing Zambia’s central bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg on  at
 mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amanda Jordan at   ajordan11@bloomberg.net  